626 Mod Launcher — Third-Party Tool Attribution
================================================================================

This NOTICE file documents third-party tools the launcher recognizes by catalog
metadata. The launcher does NOT bundle any of these tools, their binaries, or
their assets. We carry only enough information to recognize them when a user
drops their installer zip, and to surface a launch button + a download link.

If you are the author of a tool listed here and would like the launcher to stop
surfacing it, open an issue at the launcher repo and we'll remove the catalog
entry.

================================================================================
WSE Save Editor and WSE Save Fix — by RimmyCode (WSE Project)
================================================================================

The launcher recognizes WSE Save Editor and WSE Save Fix as third-party tools for
the game Windrose. These tools are surfaced as launch buttons in the launcher's
mod dashboard when the user installs them (by dropping their zip into the
launcher).

NEVER BUNDLED. The launcher does not include the WSE Save Editor or WSE Save Fix
source code, binaries, item-ID database, or any of their assets. We carry only:

  - A fingerprint catalog of zip-filename hints (for drop classification)
  - An expected runnable filename hint (for the launch button)
  - The Nexus URL where the user can download the tool themselves

Get WSE Save Editor:  https://www.nexusmods.com/windrose/mods/153
Source:               https://github.com/RimmyCode/Windrose-Save-Editor
License:              Personal use, per the tool's Nexus Mods page terms.

If you are the author of these tools and would like the launcher to stop surfacing
them, open an issue at the launcher repo and we'll remove the catalog entries.

================================================================================
Frameworks (catalog metadata only, never bundled)
================================================================================

The launcher's framework-intake flow recognizes a small set of game frameworks
(loaders / chain-load DLLs). When a user drops a recognized framework zip the
launcher offers to install it at the right location with reversibility tracked.
Detection-only frameworks (BepInEx, ME2, etc.) are surfaced via the
"NEEDS X" chip but are NOT install-capable through the launcher.

NEVER BUNDLED. The launcher does not include any framework's source code,
binaries, or assets. We carry only:

  - A fingerprint catalog of zip-signature files (for drop classification)
  - The canonical project URL where the user can download the framework
  - The author's name (so the Settings → Installed frameworks list credits them)

If you are the author of a framework listed here and would like the launcher to
stop surfacing it, open an issue at the launcher repo and we'll remove the catalog
entry.

  - Elden Mod Loader — by TechieW
    Source:  https://www.nexusmods.com/eldenring/mods/117
    Used by: launcher's framework intake catalog (Core.Frameworks.KnownFramework)

  - UE4SS (RE-UE4SS) — by the RE-UE4SS team
    Source:  https://github.com/UE4SS-RE/RE-UE4SS/releases
    Used by: launcher's framework intake catalog (Core.Frameworks.KnownFramework).
             Installs into <project>/Binaries/Win64 for ue-pak games; the user
             supplies the zip — the binary is never bundled.
